    <summary>It is argued that the previously proposed modification of the standard (flat) inflationary $ΛCDM$ model in which cosmological constant is replaced by thermal energy of expanding vacum, characterized by the Gibbons-Hawking temperature, explains the origin of notorious ``Hubble tension''.</summary>
